    <label>head scarf</label>
    <description>The keffiyeh or kufiya (Arabic: كُوفِيَّة‎ kūfīyah, meaning "relating to Kufa") also known as a ghutrah (غُترَة), shemagh (شُمَاغ šumāġ), ḥaṭṭah (حَطَّة) or mashadah (مَشَدَة), is a traditional Arabian headdress, or what is sometimes called a habit, which originated in Yemen; it is now worn throughout the Middle East region. In Iran it is known as a chafiyeh (چفیه).</description>
